FBIS3-39869 "drweu036_q_94014" FBIS-WEU-94-036 Document Type:Daily Report 23 Feb 1994 TURKEY $725 Million Loan Secured From Japan TA2102181294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 GMT 21 Feb 94 TA2102181294 Ankara TRT Television Network Language: Turkish Article Type:BFN [Announcer-read report over video] [Excerpt] Turkey has exported state bonds worth $725 million to Japan. According to an agreement signed in Tokyo, of the total loan 45 billion yen will be paid back in eight years and with an interest rate of 5.45 percent. The remaining 30 billion yen will be paid back in 10 years at an interest rate of 5.75 percent. [passage omitted]
